value.title: Former top cybersecurity official says Trump firing by tweet was 'not how I wanted to go out'
value.excerpt: Christopher Krebs, the former top cybersecurity official, said President Donald Trump's decision to unceremoniously fire him via tweet last week was "not how I wanted to go out."

value.title: Musician John Fogerty on the irony of playing 'Fortunate Son' at a Trump rally
value.excerpt: National arts reporter interviews former Creedence Clearwater Revival singer John Fogerty on Instagram Live on Nov. 28.

value.title: Not a hearing: Arizona legislators, Trump lawyers plan public meeting on election at Phoenix hotel Monday
value.excerpt: The meeting at the Hyatt Regency in downtown Phoenix is not a hearing of the Legislature as Finchem and Trump campaign's legal team have cast it.

value.title: Trump calls on Congress to help ‘decimated’ restaurant industry
value.excerpt: President Trump took to Twitter on Friday night to urge Congress to pass the next coronavirus stimulus package and aid failing restaurants as the second wave of the pandemic is forcing some parts of the country to re-enter stricter social distancing guidelines.

value.title: Biden picks up small number of votes in Milwaukee County after Trump-requested recount
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden saw a small net gain in votes as Milwaukee County, Wisconsin's largest, certified its presidential general election results Friday after a recount requested by the Trump campaign.

value.title: Milwaukee County vote recount gives Biden small boost
value.excerpt: Milwaukee County completed its recount of presidential ballots, finding only small changes in vote totals for one of the two Wisconsin counties recounting ballots

value.title: Kamala Harris called a nurse on Thanksgiving to thank her for fighting on the Covid frontlines
value.excerpt: A friendly phone call is all too normal during Thanksgiving -- that is unless it's coming from the vice president-elect, herself.

value.title: ‘Mini desk. Tiny hands. Small soul’: Trump mocked for giving speech at little table
value.excerpt: DiaperDon trends on Twitter after outgoing president’s furniture steals limelight

value.title: Federal appeals court denies Trump campaign effort to revive Pennsylvania lawsuit saying 'claims have no merit'
value.excerpt: A federal appeals court denied the Trump campaign's effort to revive a federal lawsuit challenging the election results in Pennsylvania, ruling "the claims have no merit."

value.title: Donor sues pro-Trump group for $2.5M over 'empty promises' on voter fraud
value.excerpt: A pro-Trump group is being sued by a donor for not delivering on promises to overturn the election results in President Trump's favor.

value.title: Trump team removes members of Pentagon's Defense Policy Board, including Kissinger, Albright
value.excerpt: The Defense Department on Friday said that a number of members of its Defense Policy Board -- including former Secretaries of State Henry Kissinger and Madeleine Albright -- had been removed.

value.title: After Biden win, Rehoboth Beach celebrates local boy who made good: ‘He’s our Joe’
value.excerpt: Bikinis and beach umbrellas are marked to sell. The only hint of summer is the tangy scent of vinegar-doused french fries wafting from the one Thrasher’s stand that has remained open. Late fall and winter is when Rehoboth Beach typically gets to crawl back into its shell,

value.title: Exclusive: Former CIA station chief Darrell Blocker floated to lead agency under Biden, source says
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: While President-elect Joe Biden has yet to announce his pick for CIA director, an array of names has been highlighted, and among them is Darrell M. Blocker -- one of the highest-serving persons of color to have served in the clandestine service, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Trump's furniture fail: that's not a desk, Donald – it's a table for TV dinners
value.excerpt: The Resolute desk at the White House is made of timbers taken from a Royal Navy ship. It projects pure power. Is that why the defeated US president has switched to an occasional table he can barely squeeze his legs under?

value.title: ‘Betrayed’ Black asylum seekers say Trump administration is ramping up deportations by force and fraud
value.excerpt: ICE uses physical abuse, solitary confinement and false documents to force Black and African asylum seekers onto 'death planes,' The Times has found through interviews and legal documents.

value.title: Tulsi Gabbard urges Trump to grant clemency to Assange, Snowden
value.excerpt: U.S. Rep. Tulsi Gabbard has called on President Trump to pardon National Security Agency (NSA) whistleblower Edward Snowden and WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange before the president leaves office on Jan. 20, according to a report.

value.title: Trump's continued rhetoric over election hampers recovery as Americans face heightened economic and health fears
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump finally confirmed Thursday that he will vacate the White House in January after weeks of plunging America into a dark period of uncertainty—where the fate of democracy sometimes seemed to be hanging by a thread—but he largely ignored the mounting challenges his successor is facing

value.title: Trump says he'll travel to Georgia to support Republican Senate candidates in runoff election
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump said Thursday he will travel to Georgia to support the state's Republican Senate candidates ahead of the January 5 runoff election.

value.title: Angry Trump promises rally in battleground state of Georgia
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Thursday renewed baseless claims that “massive fraud” and crooked local officials in battleground states led to his election defeat, and said he’ll go to Georgia for a rally

value.title: Defund-police supporters tell Biden they're 'not going away'
value.excerpt: Far-left advocates of defunding the police say they are "not going away" just because Joe Biden won the presidency.

value.title: Biden says family will have 'small group' around Thanksgiving table, urges Americans to sacrifice gatherings
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden called on Americans to make a sacrifice this Thanksgiving by foregoing large gatherings and noted that his own family is giving up their tradition to comply with coronavirus guidelines.

value.title: Biden says 'America is back' at the head of the table – but is that a good thing?
value.excerpt: After four years of Trump, many diplomats are hopeful – but US critics say the idea of a return to a ‘golden age’ is a delusion

value.title: Julian Assange's partner appeals to Trump to pardon him
value.excerpt: Julian Assange’s partner, Stella Moris, has tweeted President Donald Trump on Thanksgiving, appealing to him to pardon the WikiLeaks founder

value.title: Dem leaders condemn Trump's pardon of Michael Flynn: 'Abuse of power'
value.excerpt: Democratic leaders lambasted President Trump for pardoning his former national security adviser Michael Flynn on Wednesday, condemning the move as a "brazen" abuse of power.

value.title: They’re baaack: Trump and allies still refuse election loss
value.excerpt: A day after Trump said his administration should begin working with Biden’s team, three more lawsuits were filed by allies attempting to stop the certification in two more battl
